cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DB

- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses an alternative approach to spreadsheet auditing, which is a software engineering task. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the use of a modelling language to develop a shadow model for comparison with the spreadsheet. 
- cs.CY (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve some geometric concepts in the modelling and comparison process. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss the security implications of spreadsheet errors. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another less likely but possible category as the paper may discuss the use of databases in the auditing process.
